### Signal handling for graceful shutdown

Node.js must listen to SIGTERM/SIGINT to close connections and complete pending requests before exiting. Use PID 1 to ensure signals are properly forwarded; avoid shell wrappers that don't pass signals.

```typescript
process.on('SIGTERM', async () => {
  console.log('SIGTERM received, shutting down gracefully');
  server.close(() => {
    process.exit(0);
  });
  setTimeout(() => process.exit(1), 30000); // Force exit after 30s
});

server.listen(3000);
```

**Common interview trap:** Running Node with `sh -c` wrapper prevents signal propagation; use exec form in CMD or ensure PID 1.

